metadata.name: Unravelling
metadata.description:
Hanging on the wall,  
The deer looking down on me,  
Haunting me reluctantly,  
To come before thee. 

To come as I am,  
Or as you want me to be?  
The root of my agony,  
Is hanging above me. 

Lost and never found,  
Somewhat inclined,  
To ring the broken bell,  
To whom I am forever obliged.
